<subSubSection id="58D2D21669F917E0DD967FCAEB0102BA" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FA549CA5F341130C15468C9208D8E543" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E6382B738103F76F045435C7E326CC29" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This specific name is derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName id="3C07641C64A36E6B6098223DF77A6B70" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Murakami &amp; Gerstmeier &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera spinosa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis id="CF6087C05B0A8E03F17F6FFFCA437024" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(spine), referring to metatibiae apically extended to a broad spine.
</paragraph>
